A small toy project here [1] to see if I can get this notebook running...

Goal: Reduce file resolution Steps:

  1. Read a tiff file [2]
  2. Convert read to matrix
  3. Decompose the matrix
  4. Reconstruct the matrix with lower bits
  5. Display images

[1] Preprosessing Data, Biosystems Data Analysis, 2022, University of Amsterdam [2] File retrieved from: https://people.math.sc.edu/Burkardt/data/tif/tif.html

library("tiff")

#1. Read a tiff file 
#2. Convert read to matrix

USV <-svd(i_img)

N <- 8
o_img <- USV$u[,1:N] %*% diag(USV$d[1:N]) %*% t(USV$v[,1:N])

# a tif file should have value between 0 and 1 so I need to do a correction
o_img[o_img<0] <-0
o_img[o_img>1] <-1

grid::grid.raster(i_img)

grid::grid.raster(o_img)
